e7"},{label:"Business focus",iconKey:"shape8"}]},mu={label:"Services",title:"We provide the support businesses need to operate and grow better.",description:"Business moves fast, and strong execution matters. VIVIYAN CORP LIMITED offers practical support and tailored solutions that help companies improve workflows, strengthen delivery, and work with more confidence.",shapeKeys:["shape8","shape9","shape10"]},yu={sectionTitle:"Our values",sectionSubtitle:"Our values shape how we work on daily basis",cards:[{id:"transparency",numberKey:"number1",iconKey:"shape6",title:"Transparency",description:"We believe strong work starts with clear communication. No unnecessary complexity, no vague promises — just honest dialogue, realistic planning, and shared understanding at every stage."},{id:"progress",numberKey:"number2",iconKey:"shape7",title:"Progress",description:"We value movement, not noise. Step by step, we help businesses improve processes, strengthen operations, and move closer to their goals with confidence."},{id:"partnership",numberKey:"number3",iconKey:"shape11",title:"Partnership",description:"We do not see cooperation as a formal process. We build long-term relationships based on trust, responsibility, and a real commitment to the people we work with."}]},bu={ctaText:"Stay aligned with business that moves forward.",ctaLabel:"Get in Touch",ctaMailto:"mailto:info@viviyan.co",copyright:"© 2026 VIVIYAN CORP LIMITED. All rights reserved.",links:[{label:"Privacy Policy",path:"/privacy-policy"},{label:"Terms and Conditions",path:"/terms-and-conditions"}]},vu={dialogAriaLabel:"Navigation menu",mobileNavAriaLabel:"Mobile navigation",ctaLabel:"Get in Touch"},Au={privacy:{title:"Privacy Policy",lastUpdated:"Last updated: 20/04/2026",intro:['This Privacy Policy explains how VIVIYAN CORP LIMITED ("Company", "We", "Our", or "Us"), a company incorporated and registered in the Republic of Cyprus, collects, uses, and protects your personal data when you visit or interact with this website.',"We are committed to processing personal data in accordance with applicable data protection laws, including the General Data Protection Regulation (EU) 2016/679.","This Privacy Policy should be read together with our Terms and Conditions, which govern your use of this Website."],sections:[{title:"Data Controller",type:"text",content:["For the purposes of applicable data protection laws, VIVIYAN CORP LIMITED acts as the data controller of your personal data.",'If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy or how your data is handled, you can contact us at the bottom "Get in touch" on the Website.']},{title:"Personal Data We Collect",type:"mixed",introLines:["We may collect and process different categories of personal data in connection with your use of this website.","This includes, in particular, personal data that you voluntarily provide to us, as well as certain information that is collected automatically when you access or interact with the website.","The categories of personal data we may collect include:"],content:["Contact information, such as your name, email address, phone number, or any other details you provide when contacting us or submitting an inquiry.","Communication data, including any messages, requests, or correspondence you send to us, and records of our communications with you.","Technical data, such as your IP address, browser type and version, device type, operating system, and other technology-related identifiers.","Usage data, including information about how you access, navigate, and interact with the website, such as pages viewed, time spent on pages, and referring URLs."],afterList:["Some of this data is collected automatically through the use of cookies or similar technologies when you visit the website.","You are not required to provide personal data to use the Website; however, certain features (such as contacting the Company) may not be available without providing relevant information."]},{title:"How We Use Your Data",type:"mixed",introLines:["We process personal data for specific, legitimate purposes and only to the extent necessary in connection with the operation of this website and our business activities.","In particular, we may use your personal data for the following purposes:"],content:["To respond to your inquiries, requests, or communications and to maintain correspondence with you.","To operate, manage, and maintain the website, including ensuring its functionality, performance, and availability.","To improve and develop the website, including analyzing usage patterns and user interactions.","To ensure the security of the website, prevent unauthorized access, and detect, investigate, or prevent misuse, fraud, or other unlawful activities.","To comply with applicable legal, regulatory, or compliance obligations, including record-keeping and responding to lawful requests from authorities.","To establish, exercise, or defend legal claims, where necessary."],afterList:["Where applicable, we may also use your data to manage and document our internal administrative processes, including maintaining records of communications and interactions.","We process personal data only where there is an appropriate legal basis under applicable data protection laws, and we do not use your personal data for purposes that are incompatible with those described above.","We do not use your personal data for automated decision-making or profiling that produces legal or similarly significant effects."]},{title:"Legal Basis for Processing",type:"mixed",introLines:["We process your personal data only where we have a valid legal basis under applicable data protection laws, including the General Data Protection Regulation (EU) 2016/679.","Depending on the context in which your personal data is collected and used, we rely on one or more of the following legal grounds:"],content:["Consent – where you have given clear and explicit consent to the processing of your personal data for one or more specific purposes. Where processing is based on consent, you have the right to withdraw your consent at any time, without affecting the lawfulness of processing carried out prior to such withdrawal.","Legitimate interests – where processing is necessary for the purposes of the legitimate interests pursued by the Company, provided that such interests are not overridden by your fundamental rights and freedoms. These legitimate interests may include operating and improving the website, responding to inquiries, ensuring security, preventing misuse, and managing our business activities.","Legal obligation – where processing is necessary for compliance with a legal or regulatory obligation to which the Company is subject."],afterList:["Where required under applicable law, we will ensure that an appropriate assessment is carried out to confirm that our legitimate interests are not overridden by your rights and freedoms.","We will only process your personal data for the purposes for which it was collected, unless we reasonably consider that we need to use it for another compatible purpose in accordance with applicable law."]},{title:"Data Sharing",type:"mixed",introLines:["We do not sell, rent, or otherwise disclose your personal data to third parties for their own marketing or commercial purposes.","However, we may share your personal data with selected third parties where necessary for the purposes described in this Privacy Policy. Such recipients may include:"],content:["Service providers and business partners who provide services on our behalf, such as website hosting, IT support, analytics, or other technical services.","Professional advisors, including legal, accounting, and consulting providers, where necessary for the operation of our business or compliance with legal obligations.","Public authorities, regulators, or law enforcement bodies, where disclosure is required by applicable law or necessary to protect our legal rights."],afterList:["All third parties with whom we share personal data are required to process such data in accordance with applicable data protection laws and to implement appropriate technical and organizational measures to ensure its security and confidentiality.","Where personal data is transferred to or accessed from countries outside the European Economic Area (EEA), we ensure that such transfers are carried out in compliance with applicable data protection laws and that appropriate safeguards are in place.","Such safeguards may include, where applicable:"],secondList:["The use of Standard Contractual Clauses approved by the European Commission.","Transfers to jurisdictions that have been recognized by the European Commission as providing an adequate level of data protection.","Other legally recognized transfer mechanisms under applicable law."],afterSecondList:["We take reasonable steps to ensure that any international transfers of personal data are adequately protected and that your rights under applicable data protection laws are preserved."]},{title:"Data Subject Rights",type:"mixed",introLines:["Under applicable data protection laws, including the General Data Protection Regulation (EU) 2016/679, you have a number of rights in relation to your personal data.","In particular, you have the right to:"],content:["Access your personal data and obtain information about how it is processed.","Rectification, meaning you may request correction of inaccurate or incomplete personal data.",'Erasure ("right to be forgotten"), allowing you to request deletion of your personal data where applicable.',"Restriction of processing, where you may request that we limit the way we use your data under certain circumstances.","Object to processing, including where processing is based on legitimate interests.","Data portability, allowing you to receive your personal data in a structured, commonly used, and machine-readable format, and to transmit it to another controller where technically feasible.","Withdraw consent at any time, where processing is based on your consent, without affecting the lawfulness of processing carried out prior to withdrawal."],afterList:["You may exercise your rights by contacting us using the contact details provided in this Privacy Policy.","We may request additional information to verify your identity before responding to your request.","We will respond to all valid requests in accordance with applicable data protection laws.","You also have the right to lodge a complaint with the competent supervisory authority in the Republic of Cyprus, in particular the Office of the Commissioner for Personal Data Protection, if you believe that your data has been processed unlawfully."]},{title:"Data Security and Retention",type:"text",content:["We implement appropriate technical and organizational measures designed to protect personal data against unauthorized or unlawful processing, as well as against accidental loss, destruction, or damage.","Such measures may include, where appropriate, access controls, data minimization, secure storage systems, and other internal policies aimed at safeguarding personal data and ensuring its confidentiality and integrity.","Access to personal data is limited to those persons who have a legitimate need to access it in connection with the purposes described in this Privacy Policy and who are subject to appropriate confidentiality obligations.","We retain personal data only for as long as necessary to fulfill the purposes for which it was collected, including for the purposes of satisfying any legal, regulatory, accounting, or reporting requirements.","When determining the appropriate retention period, we take into account the nature and sensitivity of the personal data, the purposes for which it is processed, and applicable legal obligations.","Once personal data is no longer required, we will take reasonable steps to securely delete, anonymize, or otherwise dispose of it.","While we take appropriate measures to protect personal data, no transmission over the internet or method of electronic storage can be guaranteed to be completely secure. Accordingly, we cannot guarantee absolute security."]},{title:"Data Breach",type:"text",content:["We take appropriate technical and organizational measures to protect personal data against unauthorized access, loss, misuse, or disclosure. However, despite these measures, no system can be guaranteed to be completely secure.","In the event of a personal data breach, we will assess the nature and impact of the incident and take appropriate steps to mitigate any risks to individuals.","Where required under applicable data protection laws, including the General Data Protection Regulation (EU) 2016/679, we will: notify the competent supervisory authority within the required timeframe; inform affected individuals without undue delay where the breach is likely to result in a high risk to their rights and freedoms.","We will also take reasonable steps to investigate the breach, prevent further incidents, and implement corrective measures as necessary."]},{title:"Cookies",type:"text",content:["This website may use cookies and similar technologies to enhance user experience, ensure the proper functioning of the website, and analyze how the website is used.","Cookies are small text files that are stored on your device when you visit a website. They may be used to recognize your device, remember preferences, and collect information about your interaction with the website.","We may use different types of cookies, including those necessary for the operation of the website, as well as analytical or performance-related cookies that help us understand how users interact with the website.","You can control or disable cookies through your browser settings. Please note that disabling certain cookies may affect the functionality and performance of the website.","We will request your consent before placing non-essential cookies on your device."]},{title:"Final Provisions",type:"text",con